name: omni-banking
description: omni-banking is a banking application which follows microservice architecture and all modern technology and approach

name: Go-lang-Micro-service
description: Microservices Architecture with Go Explore the development of a microservices architecture using Go (Golang) to build scalable, reliable, and maintainable web applications. This project demonstrates the design and implementation of multiple self-contained microservices that communicate seamlessly through REST APIs, RPC over gRPC, and message queuin

name: HealthCare_System
description: The Healthcare Management System is a distributed, scalable, and microservices-based application developed in Python using FastAPI. The system facilitates the management of patients, doctors, appointments, and notifications in a modern healthcare setting. Each microservice operates independently and communicates asynchronously via RabbitMQ.

name: Stock-Manager
description: A cloud-based stock portfolio management application composed of 5 microservices, each with RESTful APIs. The application is containerized using Docker Compose, utilizes MongoDB for data storage, and leverages NGINX as a reverse proxy for efficient request routing and load balancing.

name: Cafeteria-Management-System-with-Keycloak-Integration
description: The Cafeteria Management System is a microservices-based application designed to streamline and manage cafeteria operations. The system integrates Keycloak for robust authentication and authorization, ensuring secure access to resources.

name: onboarding
description: Education start-up: onboarding service for your customers.

name: Ambassador
description: Java lightweight, high-performance web framework designed for building scalable and efficient web applications with robust support for database management, middleware integration, routing, and asynchronous execution.

name: MicroMall
description: MicroShop is a scalable e-commerce backend built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, following a microservices architecture. This project demonstrates the separation of concerns by dividing the application into distinct services for handling products, users, and orders.

name: RabbitMQ-impl
description: Producer and consumer small application,It facilitates seamless communication between microservices and is integral in handling background jobs and delivering real-time notifications, accommodating various use cases. RabbitMQ handles multiple requests efficiently, ensuring stability and scalability through its message queue system.

name: LifeQuest
description: LifeQuest is a microservices-based application designed to track and enhance personal development like an RPG. It includes Task and Reward services, an API Gateway, and uses Spring Boot, Eureka, and Spring Cloud for service discovery, with JWT for authentication and routing.

name: grocery-store
description: Grocery Store is a mobile application integrating Magento 2's GraphQL API in an eCommerce environment. This is an internship project at Boolfly, focusing on modern app development and eCommerce integration, with a Node.js microservice enabling fast and accurate product search.

name: AuctionHouse
description: This project implements a scalable and modular microservice architecture designed for efficient development, deployment, and maintenance of modern web applications. The core technologies used include Next.js for the frontend, .NET for backend services, and Docker for containerization and orchestration of the entire system.

name: habit-scorecard
description: Based on the self-improvement book Atomic Habits, this web application tracks and monitors the building/removal of good and bad habits, consisting of the microservices: NGINX, Frontend, Backend and Database. The purpose of this project was to further develop my skills in web development while improving productivity and lifestyle for users.

name: Telescope-LiveTV-backend-NodeJS-Docker
description: This application continuously fetch embed link of TV channels that are live in YouTube & keep updating the channel database. For user authentication, I have used JWT authentication. Web scraping needs more CPU, so I created a 3rd party microservice for web scraping with enough CPU. I have used Node.js, Express.js & MongoDB to implement the system.
